Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @sweet potatoes{2%unit} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Slice @jalapeño{1%unit} crosswise into ¼-inch-thick rounds.

> Remove ribs and seeds from jalapeño for less heat.

Toss sweet potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, half the @fry seasoning{1/2%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> For easy cleanup, line baking sheet with aluminum foil first.

Roast on top rack until lightly golden, ~{15%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet in step 4).

== Roasted Jalapeño Cheese Sauce ==

While sweet potatoes roast, cut top off of @cream sauce base{4%ounce} to open fully; pour contents into a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}.

Using a #spoon{} or #spatula{}, scrape any remaining sauce from carton into bowl.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}. Microwave until steaming, ~{1%minute}.

Whisk in @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} until smooth and slightly thickened. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Microwave ~{30%seconds} more, then stir again.

== Jalapeño and Potatoes ==

Once sweet potatoes have roasted 15 minutes, carefully push slightly to one side and add jalapeño to empty side of same sheet.

Return to top rack until veggies are tender, ~{5-10%minutes} more.

== Pork Burgers ==

Meanwhile, in a second #medium bowl{}, mix @ground pork{10%ounce} with remaining @fry seasoning{1/2%tablespoon}. Form into two patties (four patties for 4 servings), each slightly wider than a burger bun. Season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Meanwhile, halve @brioche buns{2%unit}; toast until golden. Spread cut sides with @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4).

== Assembly ==

Roughly chop roasted jalapeño.

Microwave cheese sauce until warmed through, ~{30%seconds}; whisk in @butter{1%tablespoon} and chopped jalapeño to taste.

Fill buns with patties, cheese sauce, and @crispy fried onions{1%unit}. Divide burgers between plates; serve with sweet potato wedges and any remaining cheese sauce on the side for dipping.